I'm here to help with coding questions. If you're looking to create a code block in Markdown, you can simply wrap your code in triple backticks (```). Here's an example:

```
// Your code here
function myFunction() {
  console.log("This is a code block example");
}
```

Replace the comment and function with your actual code. Let me know if you need further assistance or have a specific coding question!
